    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>In John Rocker's Eyes</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bernard Seeman letter quotes remark by John Rocker that suggests controversial Atlanta pitcher sees himself as victim of news media (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''I got burned by you guys too many times,'' the Atlanta reliever John Rocker told reporters while he sat alone by his locker (''In a Crowd of Braves, Rocker Stands Alone,'' Sports pages, June 28).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''I got burned by you guys too many times,'' the Atlanta reliever John Rocker told reporters while he sat alone by his locker (''In a Crowd of Braves, Rocker Stands Alone,'' Sports pages, June 28).</p>
        <p>With all his disparaging comments, a very sad thing is overlooked. He sees himself as a victim.</p>
        <p>BERNARD SEEMAN  Highland Park, N.J., June 29, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
